<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id279dbccf-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419" identifier="/us/usc/t45/s160a"><num value="160a">§ 160a.</num><heading> Rules and regulations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id279dbcd0-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419" identifier="/us/usc/t45/s160a/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Mediation Board shall have the authority from time to time to make, amend, and rescind, in the manner prescribed by <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s553">section 553 of title 5</ref>, and after opportunity for a public hearing, such rules and regulations as may be necessary to carry out the provisions of this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id279dbcd1-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419" identifier="/us/usc/t45/s160a/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Application</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The requirements of subsection (a) shall not apply to any rule or proposed rule to which the third sentence of <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s553/b">section 553(b) of title 5</ref> applies.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id279dbcd2-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419">(<ref href="/us/act/1926-05-20/ch347/s10A">May 20, 1926, ch. 347, § 10A</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/112/95/tX/s1001">Pub. L. 112–95, title X, § 1001</ref>, <date date="2012-02-14">Feb. 14, 2012</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/126/146">126 Stat. 146</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
